  "companies": [],
  "statement": "# Surrounded Regions\n\nCapture every `O` region fully surrounded by `X` by changing those `O` cells to `X`. Border-connected `O` cells remain.\n\n## Examples\n\n**Example 1**\n\n```text\nInput: board = [[X,X,X,X],[X,O,O,X],[X,X,O,X],[X,O,X,X]]\nOutput: [[X,X,X,X],[X,X,X,X],[X,X,X,X],[X,O,X,X]]\n```\n\n**Example 2**\n\n```text\nInput: board = [[O,O],[O,O]]\nOutput: [[O,O],[O,O]]\n```\n\n**Example 3**\n\n```text\nInput: board = [[X]]\nOutput: [[X]]\n```\n\n## Constraints\n\n- Inputs are sized for local offline execution.\n- Return values follow the method description.",
  "editorial": "Use the graph structure directly: traverse reachable states, maintain visited or distance state, and update the answer when each node or cell is settled.",
  "solution_notes": "```python\nclass Solution:\n    def solve(self, board):\n        rows, cols = len(board), len(board[0])\n        def dfs(r, c):\n            if r < 0 or c < 0 or r == rows or c == cols or board[r][c] != 'O':\n                return\n            board[r][c] = 'S'\n            dfs(r + 1, c); dfs(r - 1, c); dfs(r, c + 1); dfs(r, c - 1)\n        for r in range(rows):\n            dfs(r, 0); dfs(r, cols - 1)\n        for c in range(cols):\n            dfs(0, c); dfs(rows - 1, c)\n        for r in range(rows):\n            for c in range(cols):\n                board[r][c] = 'O' if board[r][c] == 'S' else 'X'\n```",
  "hints": [
    "Model the state explicitly.",
    "Prefer linear or near-linear graph traversal when possible."
  ],
